Adds a new twist into making your good ol boring desktop background into something special. You can make some cool looking themes for your desktop using this program as well as another program like rainmeter.

If you've ever felt the need to breathe life into your desktop background, Wallpaper Engine is the answer to your prayers. This innovative software transforms your static desktop into a dynamic, visually captivating masterpiece. As a long-time user, I can confidently say that Wallpaper Engine has revolutionized the way I perceive and interact with my computer.

One of the most impressive features of Wallpaper Engine is its vast library of wallpapers. From serene landscapes to mesmerizing abstract art and even interactive scenes, the collection seems endless. Whether you're a nature enthusiast, a gaming aficionado, or an art connoisseur, there's something for everyone. The diversity and quality of the wallpapers ensure that you'll never grow tired of exploring new options.

What truly sets Wallpaper Engine apart is its customization options. The software provides users with intuitive tools to tweak and personalize wallpapers to their heart's content. From adjusting colors and effects to adding audio synchronization and particle effects, the possibilities are limitless. This level of customization allows users to create truly unique and immersive desktop experiences tailored to their preferences.

Performance-wise, Wallpaper Engine is incredibly efficient. It runs seamlessly in the background without hogging system resources or causing any noticeable slowdowns. Whether you're gaming, working, or simply browsing the web, Wallpaper Engine operates smoothly without any disruptions. This optimal performance ensures that you can enjoy your dynamic desktop experience without compromising on functionality or productivity.

Moreover, Wallpaper Engine boasts seamless integration with Steam Workshop, allowing users to share and download wallpapers created by the community. This collaborative aspect adds a whole new dimension to the software, fostering creativity and inspiring users to constantly explore new ideas and designs.

In terms of usability, Wallpaper Engine excels with its user-friendly interface and straightforward controls. Even beginners can navigate the software with ease, thanks to its intuitive design and helpful tutorials. Whether you're a tech-savvy enthusiast or a casual user, Wallpaper Engine offers a hassle-free experience that anyone can enjoy.

Overall, Wallpaper Engine is a must-have software for anyone looking to elevate their desktop experience to new heights. With its stunning visuals, extensive customization options, and seamless performance, it's a true gem in the world of desktop customization. Whether you're looking to add a touch of flair to your workspace or create a captivating backdrop for gaming, Wallpaper Engine delivers on all fronts. Highly recommended for anyone seeking to transform their desktop into a dynamic work of art.

I am a 45 yo father, probably one of the oldest people playing this game. I am a single father to my Son, who is 14 now. My son got this game for Christmas in 2021 from his uncle, so we installed it on his computer and he started playing. By the end of the week he had 24 hours on this game. This was horrible for me, as it was already hard for me to find ways to spend time with my son, as he is always out with his friends or just watching YouTube. So i decided to make a Steam account and get this game to see if I could maybe play alongside him. I loaded into the game, picked my character and world and started playing but I was stuck on what you where supposed to do. I asked my Son for help and he hosted a game for me to join. I loved it as it was the best time I had spent with my Son since my wife had died. This game has ever since brought me and my son closer again and now we actually spend time together outside the house together as well. This game reminded me that there's fun to be had in everything, and it has brought both me and my Son many happy memories.

Wallpaper Engine on the Steam store is not just a software; it's a gateway to transforming your desktop into a dynamic, mesmerizing universe. Developed by Kristjan Skutta, this gem stands out as a beacon of creativity in the digital wallpaper realm.

The strength of Wallpaper Engine lies in its versatility. It seamlessly merges functionality with aesthetic appeal, allowing users to breathe life into their desktop backgrounds. The extensive library of user-created wallpapers caters to every taste, from serene landscapes to futuristic cyberpunk scenes. The sheer diversity ensures that you can find the perfect animated wallpaper to suit your mood, style, or even the time of day.

The customization options are nothing short of phenomenal. Wallpaper Engine offers an array of settings, allowing users to tweak animations, colors, and effects to perfection. The level of control provided is a testament to the developer's commitment to empowering users to create a desktop environment that truly reflects their personality.

Performance optimization is another area where Wallpaper Engine shines. The software is designed to be resource-efficient, ensuring smooth animations without compromising your system's performance. Whether you're running a high-end gaming rig or a more modest setup, Wallpaper Engine adapts to deliver a seamless and visually stunning experience.

The interactive wallpapers take things to the next level. From interactive particle effects to responsive designs that react to music or mouse movements, Wallpaper Engine transforms your desktop into an interactive canvas. This not only adds a layer of engagement but also showcases the innovative possibilities within the software.

The Steam Workshop integration is a game-changer. It fosters a vibrant community where users can share, discover, and subscribe to a plethora of wallpapers. The constant influx of new creations keeps the content fresh and ensures that Wallpaper Engine is a dynamic platform that evolves with the creativity of its user base.

Moreover, regular updates from the developer demonstrate a commitment to improvement and feature additions. The responsiveness to user feedback further solidifies Wallpaper Engine as a software that not only meets but exceeds the expectations of its community.

In conclusion, Wallpaper Engine isn't just a desktop customization tool; it's a masterpiece that empowers users to curate a digital space that is uniquely theirs. Its combination of versatility, customization, and community-driven content makes it a must-have for anyone who appreciates the fusion of technology and artistic expression. Whether you're a casual user or a desktop connoisseur, Wallpaper Engine is a journey into a visually captivating world that elevates your digital experience to unparalleled heights.

This is a game that I wished that it could been something much more, instead it fall flat in so much wasted potential that it turned from a truly revolutionary experience to a mediocre, repetitive mess of a game. 

The exploration is really, really repetitive. A lot of the structures early-game such as the Engine Behemoth or Hanza Bastion was filled with intricate details that made the world alive - people milling about tending towards holistic, artistic relics, workers scrapping by and the ordinary folk engaging in lively banter. Dont get me started on the randomly-generated events such as when workers outside would organize against the osu! corporatists or Arasaka, but the later regions are just filled with the same raid dungeons, Aurora beacons and radiant quests involving you to assist random settlements by some bloke for no apparent reason. 

The core gameplay is extremely engaging and I could spend hours clicking away and getting those quick dopamine rushes. But honestly, they're so much untapped potential in the variety of skills that the game provides that its pretty depressing, the amount of Frostpunk or Darkest Dungeon "wallpaper" skills that are just re-textures of other skills does not lend to people using those areas of magic, instead they focus on more anime-esque skills (Rivers of Blood, Warden MPX, Thu'um) that the multiplayer, competitive scene is saturated by them. 

The story is relatively strong, Act II (The Wallpaper Mechanicum) introduced new characters such as Robert G. and Belly Claw as antagonistic heads of the Imperial faction and they serve the role well. I was constantly on edge and exploded in rage everytime Belly Claw used his Exterminatus skill on some poor sod and incorporating them into its personal screaming pantheon

The OST and sound-effects are in their credit, the best aspects of the game that I have seen so far. I appreciate the music direction leaning towards a more light-hearted tone instead of a depressing one. 

6/10, would not recommend purchasing full price.

[h1] Wallpaper engine [/h1]


[h2] Lots of options [/h2]
You have a lot of wallpapers to choose from which is nice. The categories vary from like almost every game to almost every genre so everyone can find something that suits for them to have in the background. You can also upload your own wallpapers which gives you the possibility to upload wallpapers that not even 1 individual has posted yet. There is also a nice filter option in wallpaper engine where you can filter as example on [b] Resolution [/b] this will give you the possibility to easily find what you are looking for. 


[h2] Features [/h2]
The game offers a lot of nice features along with the possibility to upload your own wallpapers. You can also upload it in video format and some other possible ways of uploading which is really nice. You can also easily find wallpapers that you are looking for because they have almost every category on this application. If it was not there already then people can always upload it their selves which can be really useful if you want a really specific wallpaper 


[h2] Good points [/h2]
[list]
    [*] Some nice achievements
    [*] Lots of choice for wallpapers otherwise the possibility to upload them yourself
    [*] Easy to navigate through
    [*] More ways to upload things (not only png files)
    [*] Great price
    [*] Great quality in the wallpapers
[/list]


[h2] Bad point [/h2]
[list]
    [*] Can be lagging on your computer depending on the settings and your hardware


[h2] Overall rating [/h2]

This is awesome. Steam Workshop is full of great, high quality wallpapers. You can customize the tool to your liking (for example I didn't want my wallpapers to make sounds, so I disabled them). 

The tool can work as background service, and will work even if your Steam client is not running. You always need Steam client running in order to change your wallpaper playlist though. 

The filters in the workshop are a bit limited, but if you're using the "ingame" tool it has more filters. You can get rid of all the anime with one click (which is not something I did, but you can do it).

There are some things I think could be better. For example wallpaper history seems to show only wallpapers I choose manually. But if I have a playlist I would like to see wallpapers chosen by the playlist to be shown on the list. I have 300+ wallpapers, so if a wallpaper appears and has bugs or I don't like it, it's very hard for me to find it. If it appeared on the history I could find it that way. I would also like "get to the current wallpaper" shortcut. Some of those wallpapers have configs, and sometimes when wallpaper is displayed for a longer time I notice that the animation is too fast or something, and I would like to edit it. But again, it's very hard to find this wallpaper along all the other I have. The thumbnails for wallpapers, especially animated ones, can often be very misleading, so I need the name of the thing that is currently displaying.

You can also add your own pngs or jpgs into your playlists, and/or create your own high-tech wallpapers with sfx and stuff. I'm mostly on a "download stuff from workshop" level of the user.

One great thing about it is it stops animations and all heavy lifting when there's fullscreen app running. Even if it's just your browser covering the whole screen. The wallpapers won't be changed for no reason, and your computer resources are not being used for no reason. That also means your gaming performance is not affected at all. The tool I used before would change wallpapers even when playing games, which would sometimes cause stutters. 

There are some things that the tool just can't defeat hardcoded into windows, so sometimes your system wallpaper might glitch in for a second. I changed my system wallpaper to just be a black screen, and that made Wallpaper Engine pretty much sole master of wallpapers on my computer.

I haven't used the built-in editor, so I'll just end here. 

Fully suggest for anyone who likes wallpapers. It costs less than a meal and feeds your soul for years.

Pros:
Endless Creativity: Wallpaper Engine transforms your desktop into a canvas of endless possibilities. From mesmerizing landscapes to animated masterpieces, your desktop will finally transcend the boundaries of static boredom.
User-Generated Content: The Steam Workshop integration is a game-changer. You can tap into the creative minds of the Wallpaper Engine community, ensuring a constant influx of fresh and jaw-dropping wallpapers. It's like having a personal art curator for your desktop.
Performance-Friendly: Despite the visual extravaganza, Wallpaper Engine is surprisingly light on system resources. It's like having the best of both worlds ‚Äì eye candy without sacrificing your computer's performance.

Cons:
Potential Distraction: With the vast array of stunning wallpapers, be prepared for occasional daydreaming episodes. Who needs to work when you can get lost in the mesmerizing dance of digital art?
Learning Curve for Creation: While the vast library of wallpapers is impressive, creating your own animated masterpiece might require a bit of a learning curve. But hey, Picasso wasn't built in a day.

Conclusion:
Wallpaper Engine is not just a software; it's a gateway to a desktop utopia. If you're tired of the static and yearn for a dynamic visual experience, Wallpaper Engine is the answer. Embrace the artistic chaos, explore the boundless creativity, and watch as your desktop becomes a digital masterpiece. Highly recommended for anyone ready to break free from the shackles of wallpaper conformity!

1. For the price it's excellent, due to the following.
2. Has very high quality wallpapers to use.
3. There's a diverse amount of wallpapers to pick from.
4. Let's you download and store wallpapers that can be switched & seen in one spot for quick accessibility.
5. You can have the wallpapers running without having the app open.
6. Doesn't decrease FPS (Uses tiny amount of memory which has a unnoticeable impact)
‚Üë
For this to be true, do the following:
Start up app ‚Üí Click Settings (Top Right) ‚Üí Select "Pause" for first three ‚Üí "Keep Running" and "Stop" for last two ‚Üí (Quality settings are up to you) ‚Üí Click General (Top of Settings screen) ‚Üí Have first two checked ‚Üí Scroll down to video settings ‚Üí Enable "Video Hardware Acceleration" ‚Üí Click "Ok" once done.

Summary of what those things do: Makes it so everything is paused when you're using a program, whenever you're looking at the wallpaper if it's animated having audio from minimized program on won't pause it unless you have the program popped up on your screen. For the Quality I recommend using max for everything, unless your PC can't run it. It won't affect performance so it's worth having the maximized if possible. For the FPS I don't see a difference when using 25 or higher, but I still keep mine at 60. The options checked in the General section make it so your PC starts up the program in the background and applies the wallpaper whenever you turn your device on so you don't need manually open the app to set the wallpaper. For Video Hardware Acceleration I've heard it makes the program run better and is used a bunch.

Side Note: To get wallpapers either go to Discover or Workshop and look around/use search for more specific wallpapers. Double click on the wallpaper or click subscribe to download it which applies it. If you want to change it go to Installed and click on the one you want, to apply it either close out of the program by clicking the x at the top right or just click "Ok".

( Using "Stop" for the 2nd and 3rd option in the performance section of settings makes it so the wallpaper isn't applied at all when in another program and so whenever you go back to see your wallpaper the app gets opened again so the wallpaper takes 0.5-2 seconds or so to show up. Basically everyone uses "Pause" for those still because the Wallpaper will always be there and you don't have to see wallpapers switch out of no where whenever you exit out of a program. )

Transforming the mundane into the extraordinary, Wallpaper Engine redefines the concept of a desktop background. This innovative software elevates your computer's desktop from a static backdrop to a vibrant and dynamic canvas, capable of showcasing breathtaking animations, interactive scenes, and even live widgets. Whether it's a serene, gently moving landscape, a lively animated character, or an informative clock widget, Wallpaper Engine caters to every taste and mood. But Wallpaper Engine isn't just about aesthetics; it's a masterclass in functionality and user experience. The interface is intuitive, making the process of finding and applying wallpapers a breeze. Even more impressive is how Wallpaper Engine manages to be gentle on system resources. This optimization means that even the most complex and detailed animations run smoothly, without hindering computer performance ‚Äì a crucial factor for gamers and professionals alike. The software's ability to use videos, web pages, and applications as wallpapers further extends its versatility, transforming the desktop into a space of endless possibilities and personal expression.

The cherry on top of the Wallpaper Engine experience is its vibrant community. The integration with Steam's Workshop opens up a world of content created by a diverse and talented group of artists and enthusiasts. This community-driven aspect ensures a constant flow of new and unique wallpapers, keeping your desktop fresh and exciting. Wallpaper Engine is more than just software; it's a gateway to a community where artistry and technology converge, offering a platform for creativity and sharing. For anyone looking to elevate their desktop beyond the ordinary, Wallpaper Engine is an essential, transformative tool.

Wallpaper Engine is an application for Windows with a companion app on Android[3] which allows users to use and create animated and interactive wallpapers, similar to the defunct Windows DreamScene. Wallpapers are shared through the Steam Workshop functionality as user-created downloadable content. It features its own rendering engine and provides a wallpaper editor, allowing for the creation of 2D and 3D wallpapers, including a particle system editor and a fork of JavaScript called SceneScript for additional wallpaper logic. It also supports using video files, audio files, webpages and some 3D applications as wallpapers.[4]

History
A proposal outlining the general idea of the software was added to Steam Greenlight in December 2015.[1] The application was subsequently released as a paid product on Steam in October 2016 as an early access title. After three years of development, the software left its early access stage in November 2018.[5] In August 2019, Wallpaper Engine was announced to be one of the release titles for Steam China.[6]

In late November of 2021, the team released version 2.0 of Wallpaper Engine. This update brought a new logo, a large set of additional features, support for Windows 11, and a free android release that interfaces with the desktop version.[7]

Despite not being a game, Wallpaper Engine is one of the most used apps of Steam, being located in Steam's Top 25 played games in July 2019[8] and Top 10 played games in November 2021.[9] Users in China use it to share pornographic videos.[10]

I am 32 years old.

My ex-wife and I have a daughter together, and we adopted our son together. Both are now 4 years old.

When we were going through our separation, I felt lost and unhappy. I was self-destructive. One day, I was so angry with everything spiraling out of control that I punched a concrete wall in a moment of overwhelming emotion. This resulted in breaking my fifth metacarpal in my right hand‚Äîthe hand I worked with, played games with, and used to carry my children to bed‚Äîthe hand I desperately needed to ensure I could continue providing.

Upon learning the severity of the self-inflicted damage, I became almost suicidal. Keep in mind that just a few months before this, I was the happiest man, with no history of depression or anxiety. I had never experienced anger outbursts, nor was I the type to break down and cry, but I was in a tough situation that truly prevented me from seeing the light on the other side.

With nothing better to do, I looked for a game I could play WITH ONE HAND while recovering. Somehow, I stumbled upon this game and read some of the comments. I decided it was worth a try... I must admit I didn't beat the game, nor did I play as much as some of you. In fact, I may have played this game for only a day or two. That being said, after doing so, I had a new joy and hope for life. I managed to leave behind the pain and suffering that had been thrust upon me. I could experience the joy and happiness of other people. I relaxed for 5 ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• minutes listening to this music, long enough to realize that I would be okay.

After realizing this, I turned off the game and went back to work. My hand hurt a lot, but I was motivated. I stopped feeling so sorry for myself and became the father I needed to be at that moment, not the weak boy I was behaving like.

Today, I am close friends with the mother of my children. We don't fight, argue, or say hurtful things to each other. We are parents and friends.

Now I have 3 children. My third child is, wait, ALSO 4 YEARS OLD. The woman I am with was going through a very similar situation at the time of my separation, and we just unexpectedly stumbled into each other's lives. We have been dating for a year and are very happy together.

Moral of the story: you never know what life has in store for you, and if I had given up when all odds were against me, I wouldn't be where I am today. This silly little game helped me realize that.

[h2]Vast Collection of Wallpapers[/h2]
Wallpaper Engine offers an extensive collection of live wallpapers, thanks to the contributions of Steam users. The variety and creativity available are impressive, transforming the desktop into a dynamic display.

[h2]Performance Considerations[/h2]
However, users with less powerful PCs might encounter performance issues. While the app allows for adjustments to save power and CPU, these tweaks can sometimes lead to a less smooth experience, with occasional freezes or low FPS.

[h2]Recommendation for PC Capabilities[/h2]
I recommend Wallpaper Engine for users with decent PCs to fully enjoy the app's capabilities. It's a great tool for personalizing your desktop, provided your system can handle it efficiently.
